The #DegreeMetathon is just ONE HOUR away! Join Eight-Time Paralympic Medalist @leepster(he/him), rapper @FatJoe (he/him) and participants from around the world in the first-ever Metaverse marathon through @decentraland_foundation. Check out the link in our bio to sign up now.

#NotDoneYet #BreakingLimits

Video Description:  
-Video pans over a virtual Metaverse world with a teal-colored sky and a purple racecourse. At the far end of the racetrack is a large neon outline of Degree’s checkmark logo.
-A Black male avatar is shown running down the racecourse toward the camera. As he runs, the virtual world behind him further develops and evolves. Mountains and plants appear in the background, along with an arch that reads “START” at the top.
-The avatar continues to run closer toward the camera, wearing a prosthetic running blade on his right leg and a sneaker on his left foot. He wears a teal “Degree” running shirt, pink shorts, and a teal cowpoke hat.
-The avatar appears to run “through” the camera. The virtual world behind him transitions into a screen showing the logo reading “Degree Metathon” in neon orange and pink.
On-screen text reads: Degree Metathon. The World's First Marathon in the Metaverse. April 26, 2022. Enter at DegreeMetathon.com

latestIgtvVideos.title: Degree Inclusive-Maria
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
There are no limits when we pursue what moves us. For many people like @mariasolcampos77 with visual impairments, products and experiences aren’t designed with her disability in mind. It can be challenging to read a label without tactical packaging or instructions in braille. ​
​
So we’re working with a diverse disability community to build Degree Inclusive - the world's first adaptive deodorant. Click the link in bio to learn more about Degree Inclusive and receive updates on the prototype. ​
​
#KeepMoving #DisabilityAwareness #Disability #Inclusive #InclusiveDesign

latestIgtvVideos.title: Degree Inclusive- Nicolas
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
For many people, like @gabrielbarbershop7, there are no deodorant products designed for people with upper limb disabilities. Turning a stick or pushing down on a spray can with limited arm mobility can be challenging. ​
​
We're working with a team of experts and diverse disability community to create Degree Inclusive, the world's first adaptive deodorant. Click the link in bio to learn more about Degree Inclusive and receive updates on the prototype.​
​
#KeepMoving #DisabilityAwareness #Disability #Inclusive #InclusiveDesign
